I know this is not perfect code, but I had an old application that I upgraded to SignalRCore
and this application does this:

```csharp
            await _competitionHubContext.Clients.Group(HubEvent.CompetitionChanged + "::" + competitionChangedModel.Competition.CompetitionId)
                .SendAsync("competitionUpdated", competitionChangedModel.Competition);

            //Avoid sending all teams:
            competitionChangedModel.Competition.Teams = null;
//...send to other groups
```

The listeners in the first group receives teams == null.
That was not the case in old signalr, and the await, to me implies that I'm awaiting the message to at least be dispatched? Or what am i awaiting?
